<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF696AD6FD3394EB1D6AB9FD" bold="true" box="[719,874,690,719]" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6FC7A94EB1D14B9C5" authority="Temminck, 1840" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="harpia">Vespertilio harpia Temminck, 1840</taxonomicName>
, “ 
<materialsCitation id="74FC3CA3FF696AD6FCCF94881A70B889" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3783319627" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">
I'lle de 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF696AD6FC6594881DD6B9C5" box="[921,982,721,759]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">Java</collectingRegion>
[
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF696AD6FC1094881A7BB9C5" box="[1004,1147,721,759]" name="Indonesia" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
] ... les caverns de la partie sud du Volcan de Guédé [= caves of the southern part of Mount Gede].” Based on lectotype selection, restricted by A. M. Husson in 1955 10.*S.E. side of Mount Gede, W. 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF696AD6FBDC95C71A61B889" box="[1056,1121,926,955]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">Java</collectingRegion>
.”
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF696AD6FD2D95981D77BFC4" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF696AD6FD2D95981D77BFC4" blockId="146.[719,1312,690,1113]" lastBlockId="146.[105,1313,1119,3204]" pageId="146" pageNumber="907">
Genetically, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6FC7E95981A49B8D0" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1842" box="[898,1097,961,994]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Harpiocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Harpiocephalus</taxonomicName>
appears to be sister to the rest of Murininae or imbedded within 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6FC8892491DD9BF03" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1842" box="[884,985,1040,1073]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Murina</taxonomicName>
and related to M. kontumensis, or to M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6FC2092191A64BF6B" box="[988,1124,1088,1113]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">leucogaster</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6FB4C92191EC9BFB2" authorityName="Eger &amp; Lim" authorityYear="2011" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Murina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="908" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="shuipuensis">M. shuipuensis</taxonomicName>
; exact placement currently uncertain. The form 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6FC6592061DF7BFB2" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[921,1015,1119,1152]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Falsistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
is a synonym; it has sometimes been considered a distinct species based on differing skull size, but this difference actually represents sexual dimorphism, the name 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF696AD6FC2F92F71A31BFFD" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[979,1073,1198,1231]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Falsistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="907" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mordax">mordax</taxonomicName>
having been applied to the larger females. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
